creator: Frank Gee Patchin
description:
LibriVox recording of The Pony Rider Boys in New England by Frank Gee Patchin.
Read in English by Larry Greene; Richard Kilmer; Kenneth Sergeant Gaghan; Mark Mickelson; Marty
Yee-Haw! The Pony Rider Boys are on the trail again! This time the boys are doing something a little different. Instead of heading west to the wide open spaces, they are riding east to the Wilderness of Maine. But, as always, trouble finds the boys, in both the four-legged and two-legged form! Will they make it back out of the wilderness? - Summary by Ann Boulais
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
